<p>I wanna run "ls" command by exec(), and my code is exec("/bin/ls", NULL) but I got an text shows "A NULL argv[0] was passed through an exec system call." If I add "all" as parameter it woks.    exec("/bin/ls","all",NULL)</p>  <p>however, when I use exec("/bin/ps", NULL), it works properly. So could you help me to figure out whats wrong with my program? </p>  <p>BTW: I use execl()</p>  <pre><code>#include &lt;iostream&gt; #include &lt;unistd.h&gt;             //required for fork() #include &lt;sys/types.h&gt;          //required for wait() #include &lt;sys/wait.h&gt;           //required for wait()  using namespace std;  int main(){         string cmd="";         string cmdpath="/bin/";         cout&lt;&lt;endl&lt;&lt;getcwd(NULL,0)&lt;&lt;" &gt;&gt; ";         cin&gt;&gt;cmd;         cout&lt;&lt;endl;         string cmdCmdpath = cmdpath+cmd;         const char* charcmd = cmdCmdpath.c_str();          int x = fork();         if(x!=0){                 cout&lt;&lt;"The command "&lt;&lt;cmd&lt;&lt;" is running"&lt;&lt;endl;                 wait(NULL);                 cout&lt;&lt;"Im parent!"&lt;&lt;endl;         }else if (x==0){                 cout&lt;&lt;"Im child!"&lt;&lt;endl;                 execl(charcmd,NULL);                 cout&lt;&lt;"Child done"&lt;&lt;endl;         }  } </code></pre>